<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4597613>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIG. 29. Dorsal and ventral view of Myersiohyla sp. (USNM 550357, 47.2 mm SVL). This specimen was collected on Cerro Duida, approximately 25 km SE (straight line) from the type locality of Myersiohyla loveridgei (Pico Culebra). It differs from the two known specimens of M. loveridgei in having the thighs with irregular tan spots, instead of well-defined vertical bars, and in having the tympana inclined more medially." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4597613/files/figure.png" .
